HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1402
By Powell
A RESOLUTION to honor the Valor College Prep Wildcats girls'
volleyball team on winning the 2025 TSSAA
Division I, Class AA state championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should salute those successful athletic teams that,
through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional
ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable group of young women is the Valor College Prep girls'
volleyball team; the Wildcats recently won the 2025 TSSAA Division I, Class AA state
championship; and
WHEREAS, the program's second-consecutive state championship, the Wildcats
defeated Dyer County in dominant fashion, winning in straight sets (25-18, 25-19, 25-17) at
MTSU's Murphy Center on October 24, 2025, to claim the title of state champions and finish
their season with a record of 29-3; and
WHEREAS, the team completed an undefeated playoff run without dropping a single set,
showcasing exceptional discipline, unity, and competitive excellence behind Jentelle McNairl,
who was named tournament MVP, and senior libero Marley Maestas, who anchored the
defense as the team leader in digs; and
WHEREAS, senior Sydney Garrett led the offense as starting setter, guiding a dynamic
and balanced attack with key contributors Kerrington Corbin, a Ball State University
commitment, and Anarela Mejias, an East Carolina University signee, whose leadership and
performance helped propel the team to victory; and
WHEREAS, the team was guided by the dedicated and knowledgeable leadership of
Head Coach Kylie Harvey and Assistant Coach Lindsey McIntosh; and
HJR1402
017259
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the Wildcats epitomize all that is good in today's student athletes, as they
have achieved a premier level of success in competition while exhibiting the highest degree of
character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, their perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent not only made
possible a championship season but also surely bode well for each player's future success; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the Valor College Prep
Wildcats girls' volleyball team, not only for winning the state championship but also for the
players' superior sportsmanship and the joy they have brought to their fellow students and fans;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Valor College Prep Wildcats girls' volleyball
team upon winning the 2025 TSSAA Division I, Class AA state championship. We salute these
exceptional young women for their many accomplishments, both on and off the court, and
extend to them our best wishes for much continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
